Author: binkybarnes6969420
Text: I’m glad you were able to switch. I’ve been seeing psychiatrists and psychologists since I was 13 and I eventually just stopped telling them stuff because they would snitch to my parents. The only time a therapist should disclose what is said in a session to your parents is if you are in immediate danger to yourself or others, but sadly for minors that usually isn’t the case.

Author: SpaceWhale88
Text: I had to switch docs for similar reason. The nurse gave some tests results in an unsealed envelope to my dad to give to me at his appointment. I was 23.
